    "claim": "During clone initialization, `init()` stores the raw `rate` from `oracle.get(oracleData)` without checking the returned `success` boolean. A failing oracle response such as `(false, 0)` therefore seeds `exchangeRate` with an invalid value at deployment. Because later failed refreshes preserve the cached value, the market can stay poisoned until someone obtains a successful oracle update.",
    "impact": "A newly deployed market can come online already carrying a broken cached price. If the failed initialization response sets `exchangeRate` to zero or another unrealistic value, the market can be immediately mispriced and, in the zero-rate case, drainable before any successful refresh repairs the cache.",
